It was winter in San Diego, and I was stuck in a cold, cloudy, and windy fog in Balboa Park when I heard about an event in Vicenza, Italy. The Città Acustica festival—as the name promises—involved an evening of tycoons and top government officials and would include a musical performance by the legendary Canadian Damien Rice, along with a food and beverage competition hosted by Food Network’s renowned judges Marc Forgione and Marc Summers. In addition, there was a fireworks exhibition over the surrounding mountains and somewhere in the fog, maybe Bulbapedia, which I have heard is a big deal. Since I’ve always wanted to visit Venice, I applied through a local tourism consultant, and they put me on the shortlist of lucky guests this year. My connection with Bulbapedia, and I’m still not sure how it will help, was, I’m proud to say, arranged through our own travel website.

When I arrived at the airport, the driver handed me a passport to fill out. At first, I thought it was because he wasn’t a diplomat or a UN Assistant Secretary who was also attending the event, but as soon as I touched the wheels, I realized that this time it was happening and we were on our way to the first class lounge to watch some Italian football, Pinot Grigio.
